---
title: Hoisin-Glazed Organic Chicken with Sesame Slaw Salad
description: One of our favorite ways to add tons of flavor to any protein in mere minutes? Whipping up a delectable glaze. Here, we blend savory-sweet hoisin sauce with sesame oil, vinegar, garlic, and scallions, then spoon the mixture over pork chops just before serving. It’s paired with a crunchy, savory sesame slaw-style salad, and garnished with a zippy shower of crisp scallion greens. Now THAT’S what we call a winning dinner idea!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64403e0e3f48ada305029f59-38d14b59.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hoisin-glazed-organic-chicken-64403e0e3f48ada305029f59-5f8e3a8a.pdf
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 420 kcal
  fat: 20 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 25 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 610 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-glazed-organic-chicken-64403e0e3f48ada305029f59
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and
mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and discard root end from
@baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop leaves.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, half the
scallion greens, half the @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce} (you'll use the rest
later), and @sugar{1/4%tsp}; toss to coat. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Pat @organic chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}
per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep
warm. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

> Swap in pork for chicken; cook until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-low heat. Add garlic and
scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon},
and @sesame oil{1/2%tablespoon}; bring to a simmer. Cook until sauce has
slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Season lightly with pepper.

Add lettuce and remaining dressing to bowl with cabbage and carrot mixture; toss
to combine.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Divide chicken and salad between plates. Spoon pan sauce over top; garnish
with remaining scallion greens and serve.